quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
89,24,"He will say: “Would that I had sent ahead what would be of avail for this life of mine!”"
89,25,"Then on that Day Allah will chastise as none other can chastise;"
89,26,"and Allah will bind as none other can bind."
89,27,"(On the other hand it will be said): “O serene soul! {1}",footnotes:1:Peaceful and fully satisfied soul: The man who believed in Allah
89,28,"Return to your Lord {1} well-pleased (with your blissful destination), well-pleasing (to your Lord).",footnotes:1:This he will be told at the time of his death as well as on the Day of Resurrection when he will rise from the dead and move towards the Plain of Assembly and also on the occasion when he will be presented in the divine court. At every stage he will be assured that he is moving towards the Mercy of Allah Almighty.
89,29,"So enter among My (righteous) servants"
89,30,"and enter My Paradise.”"
90,1,"Nay! {1} I swear by this city {2}",footnotes:1:As we have explained in(E.N.1 of Surah Al-Qiyamah)
90,2,"– this city wherein you have been rendered violable– {1}",footnotes:1:Three meanings of the words in the text have been given by the commentators:
90,3,"and I swear by the parent and his offspring: {1}",footnotes:1:As the words “father and children he begot” have been used indefinitely
90,4,"Verily We have created man into toil and hardship. {1}",footnotes:1:This is that for which the oaths as mentioned above have been sworn. Man’s being created in toil means that man in this world has not been created to enjoy himself and live a life of ease and comfort
90,5,"Does he think that no one can overpower him? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
90,6,"He says: “I have squandered enormous wealth.” {1}",footnotes:1:Literally: I have destroyed heaps of wealth
90,7,"Does he believe that none has seen him? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
90,8,"Did We not grant him two eyes,"
90,9,"and a tongue and two lips? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
90,10,"And did We not show him the two highroads (of good and evil)? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
90,11,"But he did not venture to scale the difficult steep. {1}",footnotes:1:The words in the original are: fa-laqtaham-al-aqabah. Iqtiham means to apply oneself to a hard and toilsome task
90,12,"And what do you know what that difficult steep is?"
90,13,"It is freeing someone's neck from slavery;"
90,14,"or giving food on a day of hunger"
90,15,"to an orphan near of kin;"
90,16,"or to a destitute lying in dust; {1}",footnotes:1:Since in the foregoing verses the extravagances of man which he indulges in for ostentation and expression of superiority to others
90,17,"and, then besides this, he be one of those who believed, {1} and enjoined upon one another steadfastness and enjoined upon one another compassion. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
90,18,"These are the People of the Right Hand."
90,19,"As for those who rejected Our Signs, they are the People of the Left Hand. {1}",footnotes:1:For an explanation of the people of the right hand and of the left hand
90,20,"Upon them shall be a Fire that will hem them in. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
